Clear- sunny- variable winds- and slight ripple.
Clear- sunny- and there is a slight ripple on the water.
Calm- sunny.  Water level: very low.
Sunny- breezy- lake level falling.  Water level: very low.
Partly cloudy though reading taken in sunshine- breezy.  Water level: very low.
Breezy- partly cloudy- sunshine- lake level still falling.  Water level: very low.
Hazy- breezy- sunshine- lake level lowest anyone has ever seen--docks out of water- fish in lake listed on card.
Rather cloudy- partly sunny- breezy- ripple.
Very breezy- cloudy- taken during brief sunshine.
Partly cloudy- sunshine- NW winds 15-25 mph.
Sunny- breezy- last reading for the season except ice-on date.
Partly cloudy- very breezy.  Water level: very low.
Partly cloudy- rather windy- no white caps.  Water level: very low.
Sunny- breezy- light algae bloom.  Water level: very low.
Sunny- breezy.  Water level: very low and falling
Water has dropped 32" from 5/86 to 5/88- lowest ever observed.  Water level: very low and falling
Sunny- breezy- little motorized travel.  Water level: very low and falling
Partly cloudy- breezy.  Water level: very low.
Sunny- breezy.  Water level: very low.
Lake has dropped 43 3/8" since spring of 86- sunny- breezy.  Water level: very low.
Sunny to partly cloudy- v. breezy
Pt. sunny/cloudy- rather windy.  Water level: very low.
Sunshine- breezy- slight ripple.  Water level: very low and falling
Clear- sunny- breezy- slight ripple.  Water level: very low.
Ice off 4/16 (late) - clear- sunny- breezy.  Water level: very low.
No in or outlet to lake- windy- partly cloudy- taken on sunny side of boat.  Water level: very low.
Breezy- sunshine.  Water level: very low.
Very breezy- sunshine.  Water level: very low.
Partly cloudy- windy- becoming difficult to get on lake from dock
Lake level falling- partly cloudy- breezy- sunny.  Water level: very low.
Partly cloudy- sunny- calm.  Water level: very low.
Sunny- breezy.  Water level: very low.
Partly-mostly sunny- lowest lake level known- spring fed- no inlet or outlet.  Water level: very low.
Sunny- windy.  Water level: very low.
Sunny- partly cloudy- windy everyday.  Water level: very low.
Sunny- calm- last report- ice over 11/20.  Water level: very low.
Ice out 4/1- partly cloudy- breezy.  Water level: very low.
Partly sunny- breezy.  Water level: very low.
Partly cloudy- breezy.  Water level: very low.
Partly sunny- slight ripple.  Lake level: Rising
Bright sun- slight ripple.  Lake level: Rising
Sunny- N breeze- ideal.  Lake level: Rising
Sunny- breezy.  Water level: Rising slow
Partly cloudy- calm.  Lake level: Rising
Sunny- breezy- fair ripple- last reading- lake froze 12/3/90
Light breeze- partly sunny- pollen floating.  Assumed sample time was noon.
Ice out 4/16/93- sunny- breezy- migrating ducks stirring up bottom in area.
Sunny- calm- pollen on surface and sinking
Sunny- calm- 7/10/93 reading of 13' possibly due to 7/4  boat traffic- racing on no wake lake
Sunny-light breeze- brown stuff floating on surface.
Overcast- algae.  A lot of crayfish under boats never seen before!
Sunny- calm- 6 blue herons- 1 sandhill crane- 1 loon.
Pollen.  Sunny- windy - pollen in water.
Sunny- calm- algae or pollen floating on surface and suspended.  Heat wave catching up.
Lake high from a lot of rain. tree pollen in lake.
Sunny- calm- green Jell-O looking globs on boat.
Sunny- calm. pollen floating on surface and starting to stink.
Water level is very low. (much pollen).
Water level is very low.  Two loons.  Due to low water conditions it was impossible to get a boat out to get further readings.
Water is very- very low and there are two loons.

Water is extremely low and two loons.  Water extremely low as of Nov. 3- water level did not recover no matter what rainfall occurred.  Water is at least 4ft+ lower than high water mark.  We could no longer launch a boat to get more readings- it is very depressing- almost more mud than water.  Hopefully winter will bring more snow and spring will also bring above average rainfall.
2 loons- no shoreline minnows or fish.
15 geese- funny green slimy material hanging on weeds and bottom of lake
Water clarity improved slightly- still green material on bottom of lake.
Water clarity improved slightly- still green material on bottom of lake and weeds.

The lake never got very clear this year.  Most other years- it would clear up after rain and stay clear for several days.  (This year) The lake always would stay cloudy and had a greenish cast to it- even near the shore.
22 goslings- 5 mature geese- 2 loons- 18" more water than 2003.
3 loons- bald eagle.  Water very murky.  Something suspended in water.
2 loons- very much algae on bottom of lake- very murky
2 loons- still abundance of algae.  Something suspended in water.
2 adult loons - 1 chick.  Abundant algae.  Water very very dirty.
2 adult loons- 1 chick.  Super amount of algae.  Water very very dirty.
6 adult loons- 1 chick.  Large amount of algae.  Lake level very low.
3 loons.  Large amount of algae.  Lake level very low.
Lake extremely low.  Only 12 3/4 inches of rainfall since April.  Green carpet of algae on bottom.
2 loons- 2 chicks.  Much algae.  Water very low.  Very dirty.
2 loons- 2 chicks.  No algae.  Water level very low - dirty.
2 loons- 1 chick.  Much algae.  Water level very very low.  Very dirty.
Very low water- 4 loons with 2 chicks.
Fishing was poorer than the last 27 years I have been on Ranch Lake.  Water was so low it became difficult if not impossible to launch a boat and water clarity was very very poor.
Sunny- Some wind causing some ripple in water.

Lake was calm like a sheet of glass sun was shinning. Did not see Loons but usually have 2 on the lake. Also have seen more mallards than last year. On 8/6 saw a Great Blue Heron several times in the morning and evening and again this morning. Also on 8/6 saw 2 Green Heron's for the first time.
Very cloudy but calm- no wind at all. Lake is calm and no ripples on water.
